# Git Conventions

Never run `git commit` without explicit user approval. When asked to "draft a commit" or "make a commit", present the proposed message and file list, then wait for confirmation before executing.

For full git rules including commit format, gitmoji reference, and destructive operation safeguards, read `~/.claude/rules/git-conventions.md`.
